# Avoid creating large files, and abstract/refactor as needed to avoid creating large, unmaintainable files.

Large files are unmaintainable. Avoid creating large files and, when working on files that are beginning to grow to less maintainable size (> 750 lines, for example), take preventative action by notifying the user of the growing size (and prompting with recommendations for refactors). When creating plans, include refactoring/abstraction when it becomes likely file size would grow. Always make sure to update relevant tests (and, when refactoring presents opportunities to add add'l tests to increase coverage, make recommendations).

